content:
Automated invitation settings control the invitations that prompt your customers to chat with agents on your website.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.

IMPORTANT The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. To avoid service interruptions to your customers, migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

Apply settings when you create or edit an automated chat invitation.

Basic Information

* Type: Determines whether to create a chat button or automated invitation.
* Active: Determines whether the automated invitation is active.
* Name: Names the invitation. This name automatically becomes the Developer Name.
* Language: Sets the default language for text in the chat window.

Routing Information

* Routing Type: Sets how chats are routed to an agent.
* Skills: Associates skills with the invitation.
* Enable Queue: Indicates that queueing is enabled.
* Queue Size Per Agent: Determines the queue's capacity to hold chat requests per available agent.
* Overall Queue Size: Determines the queue's capacity to hold chat requests.

Invitation Animation

* Display Time: Determines how long the invitation is displayed to customers before it disappears.
* Allow invitation to be triggered again after accepting/rejecting: Indicates whether the invitation can be sent to the customer again.
* Animation: Determines the type of animation for your invitation.

Invitation Customization

* Site for Resources: Determines the Salesforce site that's associated with the invitation.
* Online/Offline Image: Sets the custom invitation graphic that appears when the chat invitation is available/unavailable.
* Custom Chat Page: Replaces the standard chat window with a custom chat window page.
* Pre-Chat Form Page: Directs chats to the Lightning Platform page that hosts your customized pre-chat form.
* Post-Chat Page: Directs chats to your customized post-chat page.

Sending Rule

* Criteria: Sets the criteria that the sending rule evaluates.
* Operator: Sets the operator to evaluate your criteria.
* Value: Sets the value to evaluate the formula against.
title: Service Cloud Automated Invitation Settings
